obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (36239)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content `This Act may be called the Jute Companies (Nationalisation) Act, 1980.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307&sectionId=36239&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (36240)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307&sectionId=36240&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "appointed day" means the date of commencement of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) "Commissioner" means the Commissioner of Payments appointed under section 14;`
  line
  line `(c) "jute companies" means the companies (being companies as defined in the Companies`
  line `Act, 1956 1 of 1956) specified in the First Schedule;`
  line
  line `(d) "Jute Manufactures Corporation" means the National Jute Manufactures Corporation`
  line `Limited, a company incorporated and registered under the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);`
  line
  line `(e) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(f) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) "specified date", in relation to any provision of this Act, means such date as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification, specify for the purposes of that provision and different dates may`
  line `be specified for different provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) words and expressions used herein and not defined but defined in the Companies`
  line `Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (36241)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Transfer to, and vesting in, the Central Government of the undertakings of the jute companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307&sectionId=36241&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `On the appointed day, the undertakings of every jute company, and the right, title and`
  line `interest of every jute company in relation to its undertakings shall, by virtue of this Act, stand transferred`
  line `to, and vest in, the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (36242)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `General Power of vesting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307&sectionId=36242&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The undertakings of each jute company shall be deemed to`
  line `include all assets, rights, lease-holds, powers, authorities and privileges and all property, movable and`
  line `immovable, including lands, buildings, workshops, stores, instruments, machinery and equipment, cash`
  line `balances, cash on hand, reserve funds, investments, book debts and all other rights and interests in, or`
  line `arising out of, such property as were, immediately before the appointed day, in the ownership, possession,`
  line `power or control of the jute company, whether within or outside India, and all books of account, registers`
  line `and all other documents of whatever nature relating thereto and shall also be deemed to include the`
  line `liabilities specified in sub-section (2) of section 5.`
  line
  line `(2) All properties as aforesaid which have vested in the Central Government under section 3 shall, by`
  line `force of such vesting, be freed and discharged from any trust, obligation, mortgage, charge, lien and all`
  line `other incumbrances affecting them, and any attachment, injunction, decree or order of any court or other`
  line `authority restricting the use of such properties in any manner or appointing any receiver in respect of the`
  line `whole or any part of such properties shall be deemed to have been withdrawn.`
  line
  line `(3) Every mortgagee of any property which has vested under this Act in the Central Government and`
  line `every person holding any charge, lien or other interest in, or in relation to, any such property shall give,`
  line `within such time and in such manner as may be prescribed, an intimation to the Commissioner of such`
  line `mortgage, charge, lien or other interest.`
  line
  line `(4) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the mortgagee of any property referred to in`
  line `sub-section (3) or any other person holding any charge, lien or other interest in, or in relation to, any such`
  line `property shall be entitled to claim, in accordance with his rights and interests, payment of the mortgage`
  line `money or other dues, in whole or in part, out of the amounts directed to be given under sections 7 and 8 to`
  line `the jute company concerned but no such mortgage, charge, lien or other interest shall be enforceable`
  line `against any property which has vested in the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(5) Any licence or other instrument granted to a jute company in relation to its undertakings which`
  line `have vested in the Central Government under section 3 at any time before the appointed day and in force`
  line `immediately before that day shall continue to be in force on and after such day in accordance with its`
  line `tenor in relation to and for the purposes of such undertakings, and, on and from the date of vesting of such`
  line `undertakings under section 6, in the Jute Manufactures Corporation, that Corporation shall be deemed to`
  line `be substituted in such licence or other instrument as if such licence or other instrument had been granted`
  line `to such Corporation and such Corporation shall hold it for the remainder of the period for which the jute`
  line `company would have held it under the terms thereof.`
  line
  line `(6) If, on the appointed day, any suit, appeal or other proceeding of whatever nature, in relation to any`
  line `matter specified in sub-section (2) of section 5, in respect of the undertakings of any jute company which`
  line `has vested in the Central Government under section 3, instituted or preferred by or against that company,`
  line `is pending, the same shall not abate, be discontinued or be, in any way, prejudicially affected by reason of`
  line `the transfer of the undertakings of such jute company or of anything contained in this Act, but the suit,`
  line `appeal or other proceeding may be continued, prosecuted or enforced by or against the Central`
  line `Government or where the undertakings of such jute company are directed under section 6, to vest in the`
  line `Jute Manufactures Corporation, by or against that Corporation.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (36243)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Jute companies to be liable for certain prior liabilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307&sectionId=36243&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every liability, other than the`
  line `liability specified in sub-section (2), of a jute company in respect of any period prior to the appointed day,`
  line `shall be the liability of that company and shall be enforceable against it, and not against the Central`
  line `Government, or, where the undertakings of the jute company vest in the Jute Manufactures Corporation,`
  line `against that Corporation.`
  line
  line `(2) Any liability arising in respect of loans advanced by the Central Government or any State`
  line `Government, or both, to a jute company (together with interest due thereon) after the management of the`
  line `undertakings of the said jute company had been taken over by the Central Government shall, on and from`
  line `the appointed day, be the liability of the Central Government and shall be discharged by that Government,`
  line `or by the Jute Manufactures Corporation as and when repayment of such loans becomes due`
  line `and payable.`
  line
  line `(3) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that--`
  line
  line `(a) save as otherwise expressly provided in this Act, no liability, other than the liability specified`
  line `in sub-section (2), of any jute company in relation to its undertakings in respect of any period prior to`
  line `the appointed day, shall be enforceable against the Central Government or where the undertakings of`
  line `such company are directed under section 6, to vest in the Jute Manufactures Corporation, against that`
  line Corporation;
  line
  line `(b) no award, decree or order of any court, tribunal or other authority in relation to the`
  line `undertakings of any jute company, passed after the appointed day, in respect of any matter, claim or`
  line `dispute, which arose before that day, not being a matter, claim or dispute in relation to any liability`
  line `specified in sub-section (2), shall be enforceable against the Central Government or where the`
  line `undertakings of such company are directed under section 6, to vest in the Jute Manufactures`
  line `Corporation, against that Corporation;`
  line
  line `(c) no liability incurred by any jute company before the appointed day for the contravention of a`
  line `provision of any law for the time being in force shall be enforceable against the Central Government`
  line `or where the undertakings of such company are directed under section 6, to vest in the Jute`
  line `Manufactures Corporation, against that Corporation.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (36272)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Power of Central Government to direct vesting of the undertakings of the jute companies in Jute Manufactures Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307&sectionId=36272&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in sections 3 and 4, the`
  line `Central Government shall, as soon as may be, after the appointed day, direct, by notification, that the`
  line `undertakings of every jute company and the right, title and interest of every jute company in relation to`
  line `its undertakings, which have vested in that Government under section 3, and such of the liabilities of`
  line `every jute company as are specified in sub-section (2) of section 5, shall, instead of continuing to vest in`
  line `the Central Government, vest in the Jute Manufactures Corporation either on the date of the notification`
  line `or on such earlier or later date (not being a date earlier than the appointed day) as may be specified in the`
  line notification.
  line
  line `(2) Where the right, title and interest, and the liabilities referred to in sub-section (2) of section 5, of`
  line `the jute companies in relation to their respective undertakings vest, under sub-section (1), in the Jute`
  line `Manufactures Corporation, that Corporation shall, on and from the date of such vesting, be deemed to`
  line `have become the owner in relation to such undertakings, and all the rights and liabilities of the Central`
  line `Government in relation to such undertakings shall, on and from the date of such vesting, be deemed to`
  line `have become the rights and liabilities, respectively, of the Jute Manufactures Corporation.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (36245)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Payment of amount.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307&sectionId=36245&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Every jute company shall be given by the Central Government, for the`
  line `transfer to and vesting in that Government under section 3 of the undertakings of that company and the`
  line `right, title and interest of that company in relation to its undertakings, in cash and in the manner specified`
  line `in Chapter VI, such amount as is specified against the name of that company in the First Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (36246)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Payment of further amount.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307&sectionId=36246&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every jute company shall be given by the Central Government,`
  line `for the deprivation of the management of its undertakings, an amount of rupees ten thousand per annum`
  line `for the period commencing on the date on which management of the undertakings of that company was`
  line `taken over in pursuance of the order made by the Central Government under the provisions of the`
  line `Industries (Development and Regulation) Act, 1951 (65 of 1951) and ending on the appointed day.`
  line
  line `(2) Every amount specified in the First Schedule or calculated in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (1) shall carry simple interest at the rate of four per cent. per annum for the period`
  line `commencing on the appointed day and ending on the date on which payment of such amount is made by`
  line `the Central Government to the Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(3) The amounts determined in relation to any jute company in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `sub-sections (1) and (2) shall be given by the Central Government to the jute company in addition to the`
  line `amount specified in the First Schedule against that company.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (36247)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Management, etc., of the undertakings of the jute companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307&sectionId=36247&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The general superintendence,`
  line `direction, control and management of the affairs and business of the undertakings owned by each of the`
  line `jute companies, the right, title and interest in relation to which have vested in the Central Government`
  line `under section 3, shall, where a direction has been made by the Central Government under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 6, vest in the Jute Manufactures Corporation and thereupon the Jute Manufactures Corporation`
  line `shall be entitled to exercise, to the exclusion of all other persons, all such powers and do all such things in`
  line `relation to each such undertaking as the jute company which owned it was authorised to exercise and do`
  line `immediately before the appointed day.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (36248)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Duty of persons in charge of management of the undertakings to deliver all assets, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307&sectionId=36248&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `On the vesting of the management of the undertakings of the jute companies in the Central`
  line `Government or the Jute Manufactures Corporation, as the case may be, the persons in charge of the`
  line `management of such undertakings immediately before such vesting shall be bound to deliver to the`
  line `Central Government or the Jute Manufactures Corporation, as the case may be, all assets, books of`
  line `account, registers and all other documents in their custody relating to such undertakings.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may issue such directions as it may deem desirable in the circumstances`
  line `of the case to the Jute Manufactures Corporation and the said Corporation may also, if it is considered`
  line `necessary so to do, apply to the Central Government at any time for instructions as to the manner in which`
  line `the management of the undertakings of the jute companies shall be conducted or in relation to any other`
  line `matter arising in the course of such management.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (36249)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Duty of persons to account for assets, etc., in their possession.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307&sectionId=36249&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who has, on`
  line `the appointed day, in his possession or under his control any assets, books, documents or other papers`
  line `relating to any undertaking owned by a jute company which has vested in the Central Government or the`
  line `Jute Manufactures Corporation under this Act, shall be liable to account for the said assets, books,`
  line `documents and other papers to the Central Government or the Jute Manufactures Corporation and shall`
  line `deliver them up to the Central Government or the Jute Manufactures Corporation or to such person or`
  line `persons as the Central Government or the Jute Manufactures Corporation may specify in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government or the Jute Manufactures Corporation may take or cause to be taken all`
  line `necessary steps for securing possession of the undertakings of the jute companies which have vested in`
  line `the Central Government or the Jute Manufactures Corporation under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Every jute company shall within such period as the Central Government may allow in this behalf,`
  line `furnish to that Government a complete inventory of all its property and assets, as on the appointed day,`
  line `pertaining to its undertakings which have vested in the Central Government under section 3, and for this`
  line `purpose, the Central Government or the Jute Manufactures Corporation shall afford to such company all`
  line `reasonable facilities.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (36250)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Continuance of employees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307&sectionId=36250&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person who has been, immediately before the appointed`
  line `day, employed in any undertaking of any of the companies shall become,--`
  line
  line `(a) on and from the appointed day, an employee of the Central Government, and`
  line
  line `(b) where the undertakings of the jute companies are vested in the Jute Manufactures`
  line `Corporation, an employee of the said Corporation, on and from the date of such vesting,`
  line
  line `and shall hold office or service under the Central Government or the Jute Manufactures Corporation, as`
  line `the case may be, with the same rights and privileges as to pension, gratuity and other matters as would`
  line `have been admissible to him if there had been no such vesting and shall continue to do so unless and`
  line `until his employment under the Central Government or the Jute Manufactures Corporation, as the case`
  line `may be, is duly terminated or until his remuneration and other conditions of service are duly altered by`
  line `the Central Government or the Jute Manufactures Corporation, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947), or in any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, the transfer of the services of any officer or other person employed`
  line `in any undertaking of the jute companies, to the Central Government or the Jute Manufactures`
  line `Corporation, shall not entitle such officer or other employee to any compensation under this Act or any`
  line `other law for the time being in force and no such claim shall be entertained by any court, tribunal or other`
  line authority.
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (36251)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Provident fund and other funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307&sectionId=36251&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a jute company has established a provident fund,`
  line `superannuation fund, welfare fund or other funds for the benefit of persons employed in any of the`
  line `undertakings owned by it, the monies relatable to its employees whose services have become transferred`
  line `by or under this Act to the Central Government or the Jute Manufactures Corporation shall, out of the`
  line `monies standing, on the appointed day, to the credit of such provident fund, superannuation fund, welfare`
  line `fund or other funds, stand transferred to, and vest in, the Central Government or the Jute Manufactures`
  line `Corporation, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) The monies which stand transferred under sub-section (1) to the Central Government or the Jute`
  line `Manufactures Corporation, as the case may be, shall be dealt with by that Government or Corporation in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (36252)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Appointment of Commissioner of Payments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307&sectionId=36252&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, for the`
  line `purpose of disbursing the amounts payable under sections 7 and 8 to the jute companies, by notification,`
  line `appoint a Commissioner of Payments.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may appoint such other persons as it may think fit to assist the`
  line `Commissioner and thereupon the Commissioner may authorise one or more of such persons also to`
  line `exercise all or any of the powers exercisable by him under this Act and different persons may be`
  line `authorised to exercise different powers.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person authorised by the Commissioner to exercise any of the powers exercisable by the`
  line `Commissioner may exercise those powers in the same manner and with the same effect as if they have`
  line `been conferred on that person directly by this Act and not by way of authorisation.`
  line
  line `(4) The salaries and allowances of the Commissioner and other persons appointed under this section`
  line `shall be defrayed out of the Consolidated Fund of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (36253)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Payment by Central Government to the Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307&sectionId=36253&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall,`
  line `within thirty days from the specified date, pay in cash to the Commissioner, for payment to every jute`
  line company,--
  line
  line `(a) an amount equal to the amount specified against the name of that company in the First`
  line Schedule;
  line
  line `(b) a further amount equal to the amount payable to that company under section 8.`
  line
  line `(2) A deposit account shall be opened by the Central Government in favour of the Commissioner in`
  line `the Public Account of India, and every amount paid under this Act to the Commissioner shall be`
  line `deposited by him to the credit of the said deposit account and the said deposit account shall be operated`
  line `by the Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(3) Separate records shall be maintained by the Commissioner in respect of each of the jute`
  line `companies in relation to which payment has been made to him under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) Interest accruing on the amount in relation to a jute company standing to the credit of the deposit`
  line `account referred to in sub-section (2) shall ensure to the benefit of such jute company.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (36254)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Certain powers of Central Government or Jute Manufactures Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307&sectionId=36254&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government or the Jute Manufactures Corporation, as the case may be, shall be entitled to receive, up to`
  line `the specified date, to the exclusion of all other persons, any money due to any jute company in relation to`
  line `its undertakings which have vested in the Central Government or the Jute Manufactures Corporation, and`
  line `realised after the appointed day, notwithstanding that the realisation pertains to a period prior to the`
  line `appointed day.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government or the Jute Manufactures Corporation, as the case may be, may make a`
  line `claim to the Commissioner with regard to every payment made by that Government or Corporation, after`
  line `the appointed day for discharging any liability of a jute company, not being any liability specified in`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 5, in relation to any of the undertakings owned by it in respect of any period`
  line `prior to the appointed day; and every such claim shall have priority, in accordance with the priorities`
  line `attaching under this Act to the matter in relation to which such liability has been discharged by the`
  line `Central Government or the Jute Manufactures Corporation.`
  line
  line `(3) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the liabilities of a jute company in relation to any of the`
  line `undertakings owned by it in respect of any transaction prior to the appointed day, which have not been`
  line `discharged on or before the specified date, shall be the liabilities of that company.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (36255)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Claims to be made to the Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307&sectionId=36255&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Every person having a claim against a jute company`
  line `with regard to any of the matters specified in the Second Schedule, pertaining to any undertaking owned`
  line `by it, shall prefer such claim before the Commissioner within thirty days from the specified date:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Commissioner is satisfied that the claimant was prevented by sufficient cause`
  line `from preferring the claim within the said period of thirty days, he may entertain the claim within a further`
  line `period of thirty days, but not thereafter.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (36256)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Priority of Claims.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307&sectionId=36256&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The claims made under section 17 shall have priorities in accordance with`
  line `the following principles, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) Category I shall have precedence over all other categories and Category II shall have`
  line `precedence over Category III, and so on;`
  line
  line `(b) the claims specified in each of the categories shall rank equally and be paid in full, but, if the`
  line `amount paid to the Commissioner under this Act is insufficient to meet such claims in full, they shall`
  line `abate in equal proportions and be paid accordingly; and`
  line
  line `(c) the question of discharging any liability with regard to a matter specified in a lower category`
  line `shall arise only if a surplus is left after meeting all the liabilities specified in the immediately higher`
  line category.
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (36257)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Examination of claims.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307&sectionId=36257&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) On receipt of the claims made under section 17, the Commissioner`
  line `shall arrange the claims in the order of priorities specified in the Second Schedule and examine the same`
  line `in accordance with such order.`
  line
  line `(2) If, on an examination of the claims against a jute company, the Commissioner is of the opinion`
  line `that the amount paid to him under this Act for payment to such company is not sufficient to meet the`
  line `liabilities specified in any lower category, he shall not be required to examine any claim in respect of such`
  line `lower category.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (36258)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Admission or rejection of claims.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307&sectionId=36258&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) After examining the claims against a jute company, with`
  line `reference to the priorities set out in the Second Schedule, the Commissioner shall fix a date on or before`
  line `which every claimant against the company shall file the proof of his claim.`
  line
  line `(2) Not less than fourteen days notice of the date so fixed shall be given by advertisement in one`
  line `issue of any daily newspaper in the English language having circulation in the major part of the country`
  line `and one issue of any daily newspaper in such regional language as the Commissioner may consider suitable, and every such notice shall call upon the claimant to file the proof of his claim with the`
  line `Commissioner within the period specified in the advertisement.`
  line
  line `(3) Every claimant who fails to file the proof of his claim within the period specified by the`
  line `Commissioner shall be excluded from the disbursements made by the Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(4) The Commissioner shall, after such investigation as may, in his opinion, be necessary and`
  line `after giving the jute company concerned an opportunity of refuting the claim and after giving the`
  line `claimant a reasonable opportunity of being heard, by order in writing, admit or reject the claim in whole`
  line `or in part.`
  line
  line `(5) The Commissioner shall have the power to regulate his own procedure in all matters arising out of`
  line `the discharge of his functions, including the place or places at which he may hold his sitting and shall, for`
  line `the purpose of making any investigation under this Act, have the same powers as are vested in a Civil`
  line `Court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), while trying a suit in respect of the following`
  line `matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the summoning and enforcing the attendance of any witness and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) the discovery and production of any document or other material object producible as`
  line evidence;
  line
  line `(c) the reception of evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) the issuing of any commission for the examination of witnesses.`
  line
  line `(6) Any investigation before the Commissioner shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the`
  line `meaning of sections 193 and 228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), and the Commissioner shall be`
  line `deemed to be a Civil Court for the purposes of section 195, and Chapter XXVI, of the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  line
  line `(7) A claimant who is dissatisfied with the decision of the Commissioner may prefer an appeal`
  line `against such decision to the High Court within the local limits of whose jurisdiction the registered office`
  line `of the jute company concerned is situated:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a person who is a Judge of a High Court is appointed to be the Commissioner,`
  line `such appeal shall be heard and disposed of by not less than two Judges of that High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (36259)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Disbursement of money by the Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307&sectionId=36259&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `After admitting a claim against a jute`
  line `company under this Act, the amount due in respect of such claim shall be paid by the Commissioner to`
  line `the person or persons to whom such amount is due and on such payment, the liability of such jute`
  line `company in respect of such claim shall stand discharged.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (36260)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Disbursement of amounts to the jute companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307&sectionId=36260&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) If out of the monies paid to him in`
  line `relation to a jute company, there is a balance left after meeting the liabilities as specified in the Second`
  line `Schedule, the Commissioner shall disburse such balance to such jute company.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the possession of any machinery, equipment or other property possessed by a jute company`
  line `has vested in the Central Government or the Jute Manufactures Corporation under this Act but such`
  line `machinery, equipment or other property does not belong to such jute company, it shall be lawful for the`
  line `Central Government or, as the case may be, the Jute Manufactures Corporation, to continue to possess`
  line `such machinery or equipment or other property on the same terms and conditions under which they were`
  line `possessed by such jute company immediately before the appointed day.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (36261)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Undisbursed or unclaimed amounts to be deposited with the general revenue account.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307&sectionId=36261&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line Any
  line `money paid to the Commissioner which remains undisbursed or unclaimed on the date immediately`
  line `preceding the date on which the office of the Commissioner is finally wound up, shall be transferred by`
  line `the Commissioner, before his office is finally wound up, to the general revenue account of the Central`
  line `Government, but a claim to any money so transferred may be preferred to the Central Government by the`
  line `person entitled to such payment and shall be dealt with as if such transfer had not been made, and the`
  line `order, if any, for payment of the claim being treated as an order for the refund of revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (36262)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Act to have overriding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307&sectionId=36262&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect notwithstanding`
  line `anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being in force or in any instrument`
  line `having effect by virtue of any law, other than this Act, or in any decree or order of any court, tribunal or`
  line `other authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (36263)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Assumption of liability.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307&sectionId=36263&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any liability of a jute company arising out of any item in`
  line `any category specified in Part I of the Second Schedule is not discharged fully by the Commissioner out`
  line `of the amounts paid to him under this Act, the Commissioner shall intimate in writing to the Central`
  line `Government the extent of the liability which remains undischarged and that liability shall be assumed by`
  line `the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by order, direct the Jute Manufactures Corporation to take over the`
  line `liability assumed by the Central Government under sub-section (1), and on receipt of such direction, it`
  line `shall be the duty of the Jute Manufactures Corporation to discharge such liability.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (36273)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Management to continue to vest in certain persons until alternative arrangements have been made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307&sectionId=36273&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding the vesting under this Act of the undertakings of any jute company in the`
  line `Central Government or the Jute Manufactures Corporation--`
  line
  line `(a) any person who has been managing the affairs of such undertakings before the date on which`
  line `the undertakings had so vested shall, until alternative arrangements have been made by the Central`
  line `Government, or, as the case may be, the Jute Manufactures Corporation, for the management of such`
  line `undertakings, continue to manage the affairs of the undertakings, as if such person had been authoried`
  line `by the Central Government, or, as the case may be, the Jute Manufactures Corporation, to manage`
  line `such undertakings;`
  line
  line `(b) such person shall, until alternative arrangements have been made by the Central Government,`
  line `or, as the case may be, the Jute Manufactures Corporation, continue to be authorised to operate, in`
  line `relation to the undertakings of such jute company, any account of such undertakings in any bank as if`
  line `he had been authorised by the Central Government or the Jute Manufactures Corporation to operate`
  line `such account.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (36274)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Contracts to cease to have effect unless ratified by the Central Government or Jute Manufactures Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307&sectionId=36274&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `Every contract entered into by any jute company in relation to any of the`
  line `undertakings owned by it, which has vested in the Central Government under section 3, for any service,`
  line `sale or supply and in force immediately before the appointed day, shall, on and from the expiry of`
  line `a period of one hundred and eighty days from the appointed day, cease to have effect unless such contract`
  line `is, before the expiry of that period, ratified in writing by the Central Government or the Jute Manufactures`
  line `Corporation, and in ratifying such contract, the Central Government or the Jute Manufactures Corporation`
  line `may make such alterations or modifications therein as it may think fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government or the Jute Manufactures Corporation shall not omit to ratify a`
  line `contract and shall not make any alteration or modification in a contract--`
  line
  line `(a) unless it is satisfied that such contract is unduly onerous or has been entered into in bad faith`
  line `or is detrimental to the interests of the Central Government or the Jute Manufactures Corporation; and`
  line
  line `(b) except after giving the parties to the contract a reasonable opportunity of being heard and`
  line `except after recording in writing its reasons for refusal to ratify the contract or for making any`
  line `alteration or modification therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (36266)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307&sectionId=36266&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `Any person who,--`
  line
  line `(a) having in his possession, custody or control any property forming part of the undertakings`
  line `owned by any jute company, wrongfully withholds such property from the Central Government or the`
  line `Jute Manufactures Corporation; or`
  line
  line `(b) wrongfully obtains possession of, or retains any property forming part of, the undertakings`
  line `owned by any jute company; or`
  line
  line `(c) wilfully withholds or fails to furnish to the Central Government or the Jute Manufactures`
  line `Corporation or any person or body of persons specified by that Government or Corporation, as the`
  line `case may be, any document or inventory relating to the undertakings, owned by any jute company,`
  line `which may be in his possession, custody or control; or`
  line
  line `(d) fails to deliver to the Central Government or the Jute Manufactures Corporation or any person`
  line `or body of persons specified by that Government or Corporation, any assets, books of account,`
  line `registers or other documents in his possession, custody or control relating to the undertakings owned`
  line `by any jute company; or`
  line
  line `(e) wrongfully removes or destroys any property forming part of the undertakings owned by any`
  line `jute company or prefers any claim under this Act which he knows or has reason to believe to be false`
  line `or grossly inaccurate,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years and also with fine which`
  line `may extend to ten thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (36267)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307&sectionId=36267&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence punishable under this Act has been committed`
  line `by a company, every person who, at the time the offence was committed, was in charge of, and was`
  line `responsible to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall`
  line `be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished`
  line `accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he had exercised`
  line `all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where any offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall be deemed to be guilty of`
  line `that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of`
  line `individuals; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (36268)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307&sectionId=36268&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding`
  line `shall lie against the Central Government or any officer of that Government or the Jute Manufactures`
  line `Corporation or other person authorised by that Government or Corporation for anything which is in good`
  line `faith done or intended to be done under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against the Central Government or any of its officers or`
  line `other employees or the Jute Manufactures Corporation or any officer or other person authorised by that`
  line `Corporation for any damage caused or likely to be caused for anything which is in good faith done or`
  line `intended to be done under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (36269)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307&sectionId=36269&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, direct that all or any`
  line `of the powers exercisable by it under this Act, other than the powers conferred by this section and`
  line `sections 32 and 33, may also be exercised by such person or persons as may be specified in the`
  line notification.
  line
  line `(2) Whenever any delegation of power is made under sub-section (1), the person to whom such power`
  line `has been delegated shall act under the direction, control and supervision of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (36270)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307&sectionId=36270&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make rules for`
  line `carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the time within which, and the manner in which, an intimation referred to in sub-section (3)`
  line `of section 4 shall be given;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner in which the monies in any provident fund or other fund, referred to in`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 13, shall be dealt with;`
  line
  line `(c) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (36271)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307&sectionId=36271&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00007_198062_1517807325307
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the Central Government may, by order, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, remove the`
  line `difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of two years from the appointed`
  line day.
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
